com.ziluck.factions.base

Interface User

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Messageable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LoadUser, MongoUser

    public interface User
extends Messageable
    The base entity for anyone who interacts with the Faction system.
    Author:
    Michael Ziluck

        Player getPlayer()
        Retrieves the Bukkit Player instance of this User. If a User is offline while this is called, the method will throw an IllegalStateException.
        Returns:
        the Player for this User.

      • getFactionRole

        Role getFactionRole()
        Retrieves the Role this User has in their Faction. If this User does not have a Faction, this method will always return Role.FACTIONLESS.
        Returns:
        the Faction Role of this User.

      • setFactionRole

        void setFactionRole(Role role)
        Sets the Role this User has in their Faction. If this USer does not have a Faction, the role must be Role.FACTIONLESS or this method will throw an IllegalArgumentException.
        Parameters:
        role - the new Role of the User.

      • hasFaction

        boolean hasFaction()
        Checks if the User has a Faction. Remember that getFaction() will not return null, it will return Wilderness.
        Returns:
        true if this User has a Faction.

      • getFaction

        Faction getFaction()
        Retrieves the current Faction that this User is in. If they do not have a Faction, this will return the Wilderness.
        Returns:
        the current Faction of the User.

      • getFactionId

        long getFactionId()
        Retrieves the id of the User's Faction. If they do not have a Faction, this will return the id for the Wilderness.
        Returns:
        the id of the User's current Faction.

      • setFaction

        void setFaction(Faction faction)
        Sets the faction that this User currently is in.
        Parameters:
        faction - the new faction.

      • getLastLocation

        LazyLocation getLastLocation()
        Retrieves the last known Location of the User. If the player is connecting for the first time, this will most likely return null.
        Returns:
        the last known location of the User.

      • hasPermission

        boolean hasPermission(String permission)
        Checks if this user has the given permission.
        Parameters:
        permission - the permission to check for.
        Returns:

      • isConsole

        boolean isConsole()
        Checks if this User is the User wrapper for the console.
        Returns:
        true if this User is the console.

      • save

        void save()
        Saves this User to the designed form of storage. This method will run asynchronously to ensure that it does not cause hesitation in the main thread. This means that saving very often causes no issues except traffic either to the database or the file system itself. Regardless, it should still be used sparingly to ensure as much efficiency as possible.
